      "algebra_tiles_make_abstract_algebra_ph": "💡 Algebra tiles make abstract algebra physical. A positive and a negative tile of the same shape make a \"zero pair.\" Solid colored tiles are positive; dashed-bordered white tiles are negative. Use these to model expressions, simplify, and (for older students) factor quadratics by arranging tiles into rectangles.",
